io.lambdacube.aspecio.aspect.interceptor.arguments

Interface ArgumentsTrait

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Arguments, ArgumentsUpdater

    public interface ArgumentsTrait
    A trait shared by Arguments and ArgumentsUpdater, that provides access to the arguments of a specific intercepted method invocation.

    • Method Detail

      • parameters

        List<Parameter> parameters()
        The parameter of the method. You may need to test them to retrieve the proper type of each argument. Use Parameter.getName() as the argument name that you may use in other methods in this interface.
        If you build your code with Java 8's -parameters javac argument, the parameter names will be those from the original code in the woven service. Otherwise, they will be synthetic arguments arg0 to argN
        Returns:
        the parameters corresponding to this method invocation
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if you try to modify the list. The parameters are immutable.

      • objectArg

        <T> T objectArg(String argName)

        The object parameter named argName. Object parameters are all non-native parameters (extending Object). It is up to the aspect writer to make sure the object is assignable to type T.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the parameter named argName
        Parameters:
        argName - The argument name, as provided by the parameters() method.
        Returns:
        The value of the argument, for this specific method interception.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if no Object parameter named argName exists in this method.

      • objectArg

        default <T> T objectArg(String argName,
                        Class<T> clazz)

        The object parameter named argName. Object parameters are all non-native parameters (extending Object). It is up to the aspect writer to make sure the object is assignable to type T.

        This is an helper method to disambiguate calls to objectArg, however it is up to the developer to make sure the object under the argument argName is assignable to class clazz

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the parameter named argName
        Parameters:
        argName - The argument name, as provided by the parameters() method.
        clazz - A superclass of the object passed as parameter argName for this method invocation.
        Returns:
        The value of the argument, for this specific method interception.
